(firstQuint)The Effect of Asymmetric Spinal Stabilization Exercise on Scoliosis.

 - Design: Prospective study - Setting: hospital rehabilitation department - Intervention: Participants are educated asymmetric spinal stabilization exercise along scoliosis curve patterns, including the location of apex and the direction of convexity.

 After performing asymmetric spinal stabilization exercise, participants are compared the main outcome measures.

 - Main outcome measures: Cobb angle, Apical vertebral rotation in Adam's test, surface EMG, Scoliosis Research Society-22(SRS-22) quastionnaire.

